      #try.info_title.wow.fadeInDown
        %i.fa.fa-download.left
        .vertical_line
          .circle_bottom
        .info_vertical.animated
          %h1
            Try Our Current OpenShift
            %span Origin M4
        .padding_bottom
          .container.wow.fadeInUp
            .row.text-center
              .col-xs-12.col-sm-4.col-md-4.col-lg-4
                %h2 On your network
                %p 
                  Want to deploy OpenShift Origin into your network? 
                  %a.strong{:href => "https://install.openshift.com/"} install.openshift.com 
                  is your one-stop, one-command deployment utility. Give it a try!

              .col-xs-12.col-sm-4.col-md-4.col-lg-4
                %h2 On your laptop
                %p
                  Want to hit the ground running with a pre-built, all-in-one OpenShift system?
                  %a.strong{:href => "https://mirror.openshift.com/pub/origin-server/release/4/images/openshift-origin.tgz"} Download an image
                  suitable for running on a VM. The image will work on
                  = succeed "," do
                    %a{:href => "http://www.linux-kvm.org/page/Main_Page"} KVM
                    %a{:href => "https://www.virtualbox.org/"} VirtualBox
                  or
                  = succeed "." do
                    %a{:href => "http://www.vmware.com/"} VMWare
                  You can read more about the Origin VM in the
                  = succeed "." do
                    %a{:href => "http://openshift.github.io/documentation/oo_deployment_guide_vm.html"} VM Deployment Guide
                %p
                  %a{:href => "http://openshift.github.io/documentation/oo_deployment_guide_puppet.html"} You can also build your own machine using Puppet
                  or
                  follow the
                  %a{:href => "http://openshift.github.io/documentation/oo_deployment_guide_comprehensive.html"} comprehensive guide
                  and deploy OpenShift Origin manually
              .col-xs-12.col-sm-4.col-md-4.col-lg-4
                %h2 Online
                %p
                  You can try out OpenShift for free with OpenShift Online. Just
                  %a.strong{:href => "https://www.openshift.com/app/account/new"} sign up for an OpenShift Online account
                  and create your first application in minutes.

      %section.content_info#v3.latest-news
        .opacy_bg_01.paddings
          .container
            .row
              .col-md-12.text-center
                .info_vertical.padding_bottom
                  %h1
                    See whats coming in   
                    %span OpenShift 3
                  %p
                    With each
                    %a{:href => "https://blog.openshift.com/how-we-number-openshift-origin-and-enterprise-releases/"}  milestone of Origin
                    comes a new version of OpenShift. And now that the
                    %a{:href => "https://github.com/openshift/origin"} Origin M5 source code repo
                    for OpenShift 3 is available, we're progressing towards a whole new architecture entirely re-engineered from the ground up.
                    This new architecture integrates
                    %a{:href => "http://www.docker.com"}Docker 
                    and the
                    = succeed "." do
                      %a{:href => "https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/kubernetes"} Kubernetes 
                      container orchestration and management system, available on an
                      %a{:href => "http://www.projectatomic.io/"}Atomic 
                      host optimized for running containerized applications
                    On top of all that, OpenShift will incorporate effective and efficient DevOps workflows that play a critical role in platform-as-a-service to accelerate application delivery.
            .row
              .col-md-6
                :plain
